        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Longford | near Derby</placeName>
                    <date>28 December 1859</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I have heard from Lord [illeg] of that you perhaps be kind enough to send me your report of the Exhibition of Garden produce by the poor. I am anxious to establish something of the kind in the Parish on a small scale &amp; any <del>kind</del> hints you might be kind enough to offer I should be very thankful for. I don’t know if it is desirable that the prizes should be small or large in amount or if it is <add>practicable to</add> require payment from the poor for admission. I mention the latter as I have found that things of this kind often meet with more success when they are to a certain extent self supporting. I hope you will excuse my writing to you on the subject</p>
                  <p>&amp; believe me | yours truly | E Coke</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
